Cell.Text: That bard Mikael is begging for a dagger up against his throat, the way he goes on about me. | I've heard him boasting at the Bannered Mare, saying he'll "conquer me as a true Nord conquers any harsh beast." Hmph.

Torbjorn Shatter-Shield. I wish someone would beat the coin out of his fat fists, the way he clings to every Septim. | He says an Argonian's labor is only worth a tenth of a "proper Nord worker." My people are not slaves!
You've having trouble with Mulush?

He's a damn tyrant. Always being goaded on by the Silver-Bloods to get more work out of us. | They pay us next to nothing. We get beaten if we make a mistake, and where are our kind Nord rulers? What are they doing? Typical.
You're in debt to Irnskar?
Too many drinking games, too many bets, and I'm too old to ever raise the coin on my own.
Who's Roggi?

He's been in Kynesgrove forever. Great storyteller. Keeps everyone's spirits up. | Owes me a lot of coin for drinks. I keep telling him not to worry about it, but he's got the stubborn Nord blood. | Damn fool doesn't have the coin to pay me back, so he just beats himself up over it, and then he gets thirsty, and it cycles all over again.
[S] He's a stubborn oaf. I don't know what good it'll do.
[S] If you want to try, go right ahead. I don't think anything will get through that thick skull of his, though.
[S] You can try, but we've gotten nowhere talking to him ourselves.
[S] You're going to try to talk sense into that Orc? I'll believe it when I see it.
[S] If you could convince him that I don't care about his tab, it'd certainly make me feel better.
I'm sure. I'm sure.
I can take care of myself. A Whiterun woman learns how to handle a few idiot men early in life.
We will make do somehow. We always have.
Sorries don't help anyone.
He'll be fine, I just hate worrying about his worrying.
You need to leave alone.
[S] Anything for my favorite lass.
You need to leave alone.
[S] Oh? Were you after her yourself? I won't stand in your way, my friend. You have my word.
You need to leave alone.
Carlotta put you up to this, didn't she? I'm sorry, but that fiery widow is mine. She just doesn't know it yet.
You need to pay the Argonians a fair wage.
[S] Well, my friend, if you think those Boots needs more coin, I'll make it happen. But I'm doing this for you, not them.
You need to pay the Argonians a fair wage.
Those Boots aren't worth the Septims I do pay them. I'm not giving them coin I could give to good, Nord workers.
I want you to leave Omluag alone.
What? Are you telling me how to treat my workers? Do you have any idea how much metal the Silver-Blood family wants us to smelt?
I'd like you to forgive Octieve's debts.
Debts are debts. Either he pays them, or his kind do.
Iddra wants you to forget about all that coin you owe.
[S] I guess if you're telling me to stop worrying about it, maybe I should just let it go. Thank you, friend.
Iddra wants you to forget about all that coin you owe.
What do you think I am, a beggar? My family has always paid back every single coin we owed, going back to Tiber Septim's time.

Node.Caption: Favor013TargetTopic: I want to talk to you about .

Cell.Text: [S] Bribing me? Well, a bard does need to eat. On my ancestor's honor, I won't trouble sweet Carlotta again.
I don't think so.
What if I invest in their future? ( Gold)
[S] Paying the wages yourself? Well, I won't say no to gold. By my family's honor, this money will go to the Argonian workers.
What if I invest in their future? ( Gold)
What future?
[S] I guess I can spare him a few beatings. Deal.
The only thing I understand is you bothering you.
What if I pay it? ( Gold)
[S] Works for me. Tell Octieve the debt's settled.
What if I pay it? ( Gold)
Don't think so.
What if I pay it? ( Gold)
[S] A true Nord would settle it himself, but at least this way Iddra gets her coin. Thank you. Tell her I'll be fine.
What if I pay it? ( Gold)
This isn't about me paying Iddra back, this is about me being able to pay her back with my own coin.

Node.Caption: Favor013PersuadeBribe: Maybe we can come to an understanding. ( Gold)

Cell.Text: Leave her alone, or else. (Intimidate)
[S] Whoa. Hey there. I didn't mean to make you upset. On my honor, Carlotta won't have to worry about me again.
Leave her alone, or else. (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.
Pay them, or things will get ugly. (Intimidate)
[S] Easy. Maybe I was being too harsh on them. By the honor of Clan Shatter-Shield, they will be paid fairly. You have my word.
Pay them, or things will get ugly. (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.
Then we do this the hard way. (Intimidate)
[S] Wait. You win. I'll ease off on the beatings, just leave me alone.
Then we do this the hard way. (Brawl)
[S] G|Think you can mess with an Orc of the Reach? Let's go.
Lay off the old man. Now. (Intimidate)
[S] All right, all right. Have it your way. Tell Octieve to forget about the debt.
Lay off the old man. Now. (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.
Do I need to beat some sense into you? (Intimidate)
[S] What? No. All right. I won't worry about the coin anymore, just stop giving me that look.
Do I need to beat some sense into you? (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.
Wasn't your business, anyway.
Already have.
That's what I thought.
Idiot.
It's better that way.
won't be bothering you anymore.
[S] Really? You convinced that lute player to stop chasing me? | I'd thank the gods, but I'll settle for thanking you. Here's some coin for your help.
will be paying you all more.
[S] You talked Torbjorn down? I'm impressed. | Here, I was saving this for a rainy day. Maybe now I can afford a few more for my people. Take it.
I convinced to ease up a bit.
[S] I don't believe it. Someone sticking up for us. Here. It's a week's wages for me, but you've earned every coin.
Irnskar's agreed to forgive your debt.
[S] You've done a fine thing for me. You know, I used to be quite a warrior in my day. Let me show you a thing or two.
Roggi won't be complaining anymore.
[S] It'll be good to not have to hear him whining about his debts. | Roggi pawned a few of his things back when he still had things to pawn. Take them.
She's not yours. Stop this nonsense. (Persuade)
[S] Maybe you're right. I guess I just didn't want anyone to think I couldn't handle one Nord lass. | On my honor, I won't bother Carlotta ever again.
She's not yours. Stop this nonsense. (Persuade)
What did you just say? All I heard was the sound of jealousy.
They'll work harder if you pay them more. (Persuade)
[S] Bold words, but true. Fine, you win. I'll pay the Argonians more coin.
They'll work harder if you pay them more. (Persuade)
They don't work now. Why should I waste more money?
You're working him to death. Lay off. (Persuade)
[S] All right, all right. You sound like a damn Legion officer, but I get it. I'll give him a break. This better not hurt our quota.
You're working him to death. Lay off. (Persuade)
I'm in charge of the smelter. Not you. So why don't you lay off?
He's an old man. Let it go. (Persuade)
[S] Fine. You sound like a priest of Mara, but I get your point. Tell him to forget about the gold.
He's an old man. Let it go. (Persuade)
A debt. Is a debt.
Stop being stubborn. Let it go. (Persuade)
[S] I guess you're right. A Nord shouldn't be so proud to turn down a kind soul's generosity. Tell Iddra I'll be fine.
Stop being stubborn. Let it go. (Persuade)
No. I have my pride.
